Fedora
------

From scripts/:

    ./download   # install packages
    ./install    # symlink dotfiles into $HOME (idempotent)

Neovim
------

Config lives in nvim/ (Lua + lazy.nvim). On first `nvim` launch, lazy.nvim
bootstraps itself and installs the plugins (treesitter + lualine); treesitter
parsers install per language automatically. No manual setup needed.

Vim (legacy)
------------

Plain `vim` still uses vimrc + Vundle:

    git clone https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim
    vim +PluginInstall +qall
